Simulation & Scenario Engine (SIM)
Documentation Master Plan (Aligned to NS-GGP Canonical Template)
PurposeThis document defines the authoritative documentation master plan for SIM, strictly aligned to the existing NS-GGP document structure (000–014).
SIM is the counterfactual reasoning and scenario evaluation engine for Northfield Solidarity. It evaluates what could happen under different assumptions before execution is authorized. SIM does not execute actions (DAT), record financial truth (FLO), or govern approvals (GGP).

SIM Documentation Index (Canonical)

NS-SIM-000 — CHARTER
Purpose: Define why SIM exists
Scope:
Mission of SIM
Why scenario testing is required before execution
SIM’s role in reducing downside risk
Explicit non-goals (execution, governance, accounting)
Mirrors: NS-GGP-000

